About Mohammed Saiful Alam My work: Retired Professor, Civil Engineering Department, BUET, Dhaka, Bangladesh
Speaks Bengali, English, Hindi, and Japanese
Lives in Dhaka, Bangladesh
I am a retired Professor of Civil Engineering, BUET, Dhaka, Bangladesh. Originally I am from Dhaka, Bangladesh. I worked at the Bangladesh University of Engineering & Technology (BUET) for the last 25 years. I love teaching my students, and doing research in the numerical analysis of nonlinear FEM, ANN, GA, etc. In my leisure time, I enjoy watching movies and listening to music. I love to play squash and tennis. I walk for one and half hours every night along with my lovely wife.

About Mir I spend too much time: Watching Theaters, Movies & Series
My biography title: Storyteller
Speaks Bengali and English
Lives in Dhaka, Bangladesh
I am a passionate filmmaker who enjoys telling stories through visual mediums. Apart from that I love to open up my home as a host. Sharing my love for hospitality and adventure with others is just as fulfilling as bringing my creative visions to life on screen.

My name is Aiman Saad Hamid, I was born and bought up in my home in Dhaka, Cantonment. I finished my schooling in The Aga Khan School, Dhaka and currently pursuing my major in Computer Science and Engineering in Independent University of Bangladesh. I love eating but staying fit at the same time. I enjoy playing chess as I was taught by my grandmother Rani Hamid who holds the WIM title internationally.
